text: Full Gear (2020) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on November 7, 2020, mainly at the Daily's Place in Jacksonville, Florida. It was the second Full Gear event held by AEW. The main event saw Jon Moxley defeat Eddie Kingston in an "I Quit" match to keep his AEW World Championship. Moxley hit Kingston with the Paradigm Shift. He then wrapped barbed wire around his own arm and applied the bulldog choke on Kingston to make him say the words "I quit".
